reviewText: C. Thomas Howell stars as Lyndon Harris, a local sheriff of a sleepy, Northwestern farm town that uses bees to pollinate their organically grown produce. However, among this year's crop is a gang of killer bees that savagely attack all that move. For Lyndon, it's his worst nightmare come true - he's terrified of bees.When a huge swarm descends on the town, a group of townspeople, including his family, become trapped by the swarm and Lyndon must face his biggest fear to save them.
